<reference id="reference_F0EE68EBB2EF4EB0A087000BEB7E1283">
  <title>Redirector Constraints</title>
  <shortdesc>There are some constraints on the use of a redirector. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Target" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Advanced" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <refbody>
    <refsyn id="refsyn_65E002418E62476BB0F8278E2E8675B9">
      <p>
        <ul id="ul_C90FAEADA5AA41178707906FAED8A9D5">
          <li id="li_251BAA239D394FBAAD76DA2ECEFA9EE2">There is no client side
			 timeout as with standard mboxes. If Target is ever completely down (almost
			 never) a visitor cannot click to your destination. 
		  </li>
          <li id="li_E6E9163784FE45D4AB51D5D59BF27BF9">Third party cookies are
			 used to track the clicks on the ad. If the PCIds are different, by default
			 Test&amp;Target merges the visitor's third party with any existing first party
			 profiles. 
		  </li>
          <li id="li_CAFBB6EF281B4D47A452B7F1888FDF01">To use first party cookies
			 to track ad clicks, pass the mbox session in the URL. Talk to your account
			 representative to do this. 
		  </li>
        </ul>
      </p>
    </refsyn>
  </refbody>
